# Kill Chain — Orphan Code Audit

**Audited:** 2026-03-23  
**Severity:** CRITICAL — Kill Chain layers reading zero on production despite live data

---

## 1. Verified Architecture (Two Separate Kill Chain Systems)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> There are **two independent kill chain implementations** that do not talk to each other. This is the root cause of the confusion.

| System | File | Used By |
|--------|------|---------|
| **Scorer (active)** | `backend/app/signals/kill_chain.py` | `/api/v1/signals` → Signals page |
| **Full Scanner (legacy)** | `live_monitoring/enrichment/apis/kill_chain_engine.py` | Not called by any API endpoint |

---

## 2. What IS Wired (Scorer — `kill_chain.py`)

```python
# Layer 1: Brain Manager  ✅ WIRED
brain = BrainManager().get_report(use_cache=True)
boost = brain.get("divergence_boost", 0)

# Layer 2: COT Divergence  ✅ WIRED (but named differently)
cot = COTClient(cache_ttl=3600).get_divergence_signal("ES")
specs = cot.get("specs_net", 0)
# → bullish_pts or bearish_pts, NOT a binary "triggered" flag

# Layer 3: GEX Regime  ✅ WIRED
gex_calc = GEXCalculator(cache_ttl=300)
gex_result = gex_calc.compute_gex("SPX")
regime = gex_result.gamma_regime
# → bearish_pts += 2 if NEGATIVE + SV > 55%
```

