## 4. Correction to the Original Diagnosis

> [!NOTE]
> The original diagnosis slightly misidentified the root cause.

| Claim | Reality |
|-------|---------|
| "KillChainEngine never calls get_cot_signal()" | ❌ Wrong — `kill_chain.py:L65` calls `get_divergence_signal("ES")` |
| "VIX/VIX3M ratio not being calculated" | ✅ Correct — ratio is never computed. GEX layer only checks regime string |
| "DVR module never wired" | ✅ Mostly correct — `sv_pct` IS read in GEX eval but never surfaced as its own layer |
| "entry_price not persisting" | ✅ Correct — field was never built |
| "Layer cards display zero" | ✅ Correct — but cause is missing structured `layer_1/2/3` keys, not missing data fetches |

